item.title: Split Tray for Galaxy Trucker 2021 Insert
item.description:
The set of inserts for the 2021 edition of Galaxy Trucker designed by Northernmenace located here is great.

https://www.thingiverse.com/thing:5002715

However, the top tray for holding the tiles, boards and manuals is quite large and won't fit my printer. I made a split tray design to replace the large tray in his insert. The inner edge is lower so it will hold the tiles but allow room for the longer boards and manuals to sit on top above the inner lip. See the photos.

Print two copies of the tray and place them with the lower edges aligned in the center. It works well for me. Thanks, Northernmenace, for such a great overall insert.
item.author: coolerthanmilk

item.title: FETtec (KISS) Babytooth canopy nano camera
item.description:
Hej,

I have designed a 3,5" toothpick frame for the FETtec 15A AIO board. The frame can take actually both normal whoop AIO boards on 25,5 x 25,5 mm mounting pattern.

If you decide to build with the FETtec board the normal whoop orientation camera mounts or canopies probably will not work due to the 45-degrees angle difference.

Here comes my canopy into the picture. It can mounted on top of the FETtec AIO board similarly as you would do on normal toothpicks with the BeeBrain v2 canopy or other products.

I have made the mount for 14 mm nano cameras, with large lenses. So cameras like (and not exclusive to below list):

  • RunCam Racer Nano series
  • RunCam Nano 4
  • Foxeer Toothless 2 Nano (and Starlight Nano)
  • Caddx Ant Lite FPV Cycle Edition
item.author: akomives

item.title: Indicator Holder Ender 3 pro
item.description:
Hello, I found a dial indicator holder for my Ender 3 printer here,
downloaded it and printed it out.
But I quickly realized that it wasn't optimal, so I redesigned and improved it.
This design is now so that the dial gauge hangs a little higher so that you no longer need to move in Z after Auto Home and setting the Z height. In addition, the fan is no longer completely covered. Then this holder is designed in such a way that it can be printed from a plane without support material, the holes are suitable for my Garant brand digital dial indicator

item.title: Ball vise
item.description:
Here at Thingiverse we found a similar device but I wanted to make mine with some things that I believe will make it easier to print and handle.

I believe the tolerance between the parts is in line with my machine's configuration and calibration. If you have difficulty with the master screw threading, please use the horizontal size compensation of your preferred slicer.

As a reference the ball is 100mm in diameter but I was also able to make one on a smaller scale with 70% of the original size.

The filling of the ball you can put iron filings or other heavy thing equally

Happy 3d printing!

item.title: MST RMX 2.0 Lambo high motor mount cover
item.description:
This is for the MST RMX 2.0 with the lambo body. Doing the high motor mount forces you to raise the body or cut a hole. This fake motor cover will make for a nice addition along with cover the hole you have to cut and keep your body nice and low.

The template is just to keep you from cutting to much of a hole. (will need to trim a little more then the temple outline. more or less just a starting point.) I did my measurements from the inside of the body. Turbos facing the rear i put the temple about 3mm back from the bottom of the rear window. keep in mind this was for my body and how i have it mounted on my chassis. my best advise is to flip the motor, put the body on and then do your best to trace out where the motor sits.then go from there. Good luck!

P:S:
There are some supports i was unable to remove. They are under the intake. Instead of risking breaking something i left mine and it didn't effect the over all look.

item.description: This is a remix of DWS_design's V3_TOP_DRAWER. item.title: D4x2mm Disc Magnet Driver
item.description:
During our latest KS campaign (Make 100 Character & Dice Storage Boxes, http://kck.st/3KvQrV7) we became worried about installing all the magnets in the printed Tomes and getting the alignment of the magnets perfect. As a result, we developed a "magnet driver" which we can use to ensure each magnet is glued in in the correct orientation every time. We thought we'd share this little innovation with you!

After gluing in a d4x2mm disc magnet, you can use this as a simple magnet tool to pick up lightweight metal objects, or to align the insertion and placement of other magnets to ensure the polarity is in the correct direction. Use with a 2nd driver with a magnet in the opposite direction to place opposing magnets for doors, cases or whatever!

item.description:
